A vintage 1970s technical illustration style image depicting an intricate brass padlock with multiple keyholes arranged in a branching tree pattern, each keyhole labeled with a small ornate nameplate. The padlock sits atop a stack of weathered manila folders and punch cards. Warm sepia tones dominate, with aged paper textures and subtle coffee stains on the background. Delicate crosshatching shadows give depth to the mechanical details. In the background, faded blueprint-style diagrams show interconnected network nodes resembling an old telephone switchboard. The composition evokes the complexity of managing multiple identities and access points through a single authentication system, rendered in the aesthetic of vintage technical manuals and patent drawings.
